{"id": "13950", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13950", "title": "Heal", "text": "Heal is a &lt;a href=\"Priest%23Holy\"&gt;Holy&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; healing spell. It is the largest single-target direct heal available to the class, and the spell of choice if your target needs a large amount of healing, but isn't in any immediate danger. It is the slower but more affordable heal, as opposed to the faster but less cost effective &lt;a href=\"Flash%20Heal\"&gt;Flash Heal&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "13948", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13948", "title": "Heal (Classic)", "text": "Heal was a &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; healing ability. It covers the niche of a cheap heal that can be cast virtually forever. The downside is that it is slow to cast and not very powerful. For a far more powerful but less efficient healing spell, use &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Heal%20%28Classic%29\"&gt;Greater Heal (Classic)&lt;/a&gt;. In situations where speed takes priority over mana efficiency, the quick but expensive &lt;a href=\"Flash%20Heal\"&gt;Flash Heal&lt;/a&gt; may be preferred. While both these spells are undeniably more powerful, Heal is more mana efficient, and is a spell that can be used as a filler when nothing much else is going on. \nWarcraft III Manual background.\n\"The positive energies of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; can be channeled to create a healing energy wave. This technique, developed first by the &lt;a href=\"High%20elf\"&gt;high elves&lt;/a&gt;, and later taught to &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s, has remained relatively unchanged since its original discovery.\""}
