{"id": "330623", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=330623", "title": "Healing the Wounded (Horde)", "text": "Objectives.\nLearn Flash Heal from Matron Arena. Practice casting Flash Heal 5 times on Wounded Outrunners.\nDescription.\nThe time has come for your first lesson in the healing arts. I want to teach you a very basic healing spell that you can use to quickly heal the injuries of an ally.\nOnce we've finished our lesson, I want you to practice your new healing skills on some of the wounded outrunners who have taken refuge in the Sunspire.\nRewards.\nYou will receive:\nProgress.\nWell?\nCompletion.\nAh good, a &lt;class&gt;. I've been expecting you.\nThere are a few tasks that I have which you are particularly suited to."}
{"id": "639966", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=639966", "title": "Healing ward", "text": "Healing wards are &lt;a href=\"totem\"&gt;totem&lt;/a&gt;s that can be used for healing. They are most commonly used by &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn Warcraft III.\nIn \"\", healing wards are mainly employed by &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Witch%20Doctor%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;troll witch doctor&lt;/a&gt;s, although can be bought by &lt;a href=\"Hero%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; units.\nIn the RPG.\nHealing wards are Horde totems decorated with fearsome faces to scare away evil spirits. They are also charged with magical power by Horde shamans to mend the wounds of warriors who rally to the healing wards on the battlefield."}
