{"id": "19693", "revid": "40372170", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19693", "title": "Health regeneration", "text": "The rate at which &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; points regenerate is referred to as health regeneration.\nThe Health regeneration has Changed with &lt;a href=\"Patch_4.0.1_%28undocumented_changes%29\"&gt;Patch 4.0.1&lt;/a&gt;. \"Health regeneration uses a new formula. Outside of combat, all classes regenerate a percentage of their maximum health per second before the effects of abilities.\"\nCombat.\nNo health regeneration occurs during combat, with the exception of the troll racial ability &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28racial%29\"&gt;Regeneration (racial)&lt;/a&gt;.\nDespite this, items that either say \"Restores X health [every|per] 5 sec.\" or \"+X Health Regeneration\" will regenerate health at all times (even during combat). One point of \"Health Regeneration\" is the same as 1 health every 5 seconds."}
