{"id": "700255", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=700255", "title": "Hearing Aid", "text": "Objectives.\nPlace the &lt;a href=\"Aural%20Sequencer\"&gt;Aural Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Desmotaeron\"&gt;Desmotaeron&lt;/a&gt; to help &lt;a href=\"Ve%27nari\"&gt;Ve'nari&lt;/a&gt; eavesdrop on the inhabitants.\nDescription.\nHow fortuitous! You just happened to be transferred to a location in which I have a certain... interest. Place the aural sequencers I gave you and I will attempt to establish a functional signal.\nSuch a perilous location will require the utmost discretion. You will want to use your ethereal cloak to avoid being seen.\nRewards.\nYou will receive:\nProgress.\nWe do not yet have a good signal. Place the aural sequencers.\nCompletion.\nPerfect. Their secrets will soon be mine.\nPardon me. I meant to say \"ours.\"\nNotes.\nOn accept:\nPlayers gain a bonus ability:\nUse the cloak to gain an untimed &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;-style buff. Steer clear of the soulseekers and dusksavages, which have truesight. Enter &lt;a href=\"Desmotaeron\"&gt;Desmotaeron&lt;/a&gt; itself, where the gates have opened and the Grave Chill debuff has lifted. Head in and look for the Aural Sequencer Prime and interact with it. Note that this will break the cloak's invisiblity, so be wary!\nThe next sequencer is to the southeast, tucked under a platform:\nFollow the stairs down to the north. Walk past two Maldraxxi Defectors:\nApproach the final Aural Sequencer:\nInteract with it and Ve'nari's projection will appear to turn in the quest.\nThere are two &lt;a href=\"Treasures%20of%20Korthia\"&gt;Treasures of Korthia&lt;/a&gt; also in Desmotaeron, the &lt;a href=\"Helsworn%20Chest\"&gt;Helsworn Chest&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Jeweled%20Heart%20of%20Ezekiel\"&gt;Jeweled Heart of Ezekiel&lt;/a&gt;. Note that attempting to loot either will break the invisibility buff!"}
{"id": "623834", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=623834", "title": "Heart", "text": "Heart was a &lt;a href=\"yeti\"&gt;yeti&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Feral%20Scar\"&gt;Feral Scar&lt;/a&gt; and a sister of the &lt;a href=\"Feral%20Scar%20%28Traveler%29\"&gt;tribe's leader with the same name&lt;/a&gt;. She was killed by the &lt;a href=\"Gordunni\"&gt;Gordunni&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;s who invaded the haven, their home."}
{"id": "212207", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=212207", "title": "Heart's Blood Shrine", "text": "Heart's Blood Shrine is a &lt;a href=\"furbolg\"&gt;furbolg&lt;/a&gt; shire located far east of &lt;a href=\"Conquest%20Hold\"&gt;Conquest Hold&lt;/a&gt; and past &lt;a href=\"Rage%20Fang%20Shrine\"&gt;Rage Fang Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, in the &lt;a href=\"Grizzly%20Hills\"&gt;Grizzly Hills&lt;/a&gt;. It is controlled by &lt;a href=\"Redfang%20Hunter\"&gt;hunters&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Redfang%20Elder\"&gt;elders&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Redfang%20tribe\"&gt;Redfang tribe&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt also here that lives the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20guardian\"&gt;Ancient guardian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Kodian\"&gt;Kodian&lt;/a&gt;, the daughter of &lt;a href=\"Ursoc\"&gt;Ursoc&lt;/a&gt; and niece of &lt;a href=\"Ursol\"&gt;Ursol&lt;/a&gt;. In fact, she is a prisoner of a sort, as the mad furbolgs won't allow her to leave, and because she loves her people, she would rather stay put than hurt any of them.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"war%20against%20the%20Jailer\"&gt;war against the Jailer&lt;/a&gt;, the brothers &lt;a href=\"Bronzebeard\"&gt;Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt; managed to slip past the furbolgs to speak with Kodian, who was still present in the shrine to continue her duty. She explained that her brother &lt;a href=\"Orsonn\"&gt;Orsonn&lt;/a&gt; is also still prisoner at &lt;a href=\"Rage%20Fang%20Shrine\"&gt;Rage Fang Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, and that both of them still hope that someday their people will find peace among themselves. She also answered their questions about their &lt;a href=\"Mina%20Stormsmith\"&gt;mysterious ancestor&lt;/a&gt;."}
