{"id": "335781", "revid": "40372170", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=335781", "title": "Heart of Fear", "text": "Heart of Fear is one of the three launch raids that opened in \"\". This is the seat of the &lt;a href=\"mantid\"&gt;mantid&lt;/a&gt; dominion, and a place where &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Empress%20Shek%27zeer\"&gt;the queen of the mantid&lt;/a&gt; currently resides, possessed by the &lt;a href=\"Sha%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Sha of Fear&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe entrance to this raid dungeon is in the base of a large rotting tree structure in the west of the &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Wastes\"&gt;Dread Wastes&lt;/a&gt;.\nNormal mode opened October 30, 2012, first Raid Finder part and Heroic modes opened on November 6, 2012, and second Raid Finder part opened on November 13, 2012. Raid Finder difficulty requires an average item level of 470.\nBackground.\nDungeon Journal.\n\"The &lt;a href=\"Sha%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Sha of Fear&lt;/a&gt; has corrupted the grand empress of the &lt;a href=\"mantid\"&gt;mantid&lt;/a&gt;. Her increasingly erratic and paranoid commands have driven the &lt;a href=\"Klaxxi\"&gt;Klaxxi&lt;/a&gt;--the keepers of mantid culture--to take aggressive action. Because they are few in number, the Klaxxi are reluctantly willing to accept &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;outside help&lt;/a&gt; in destroying the empress and purging their race of the &lt;a href=\"sha\"&gt;sha&lt;/a&gt;'s negative influence.\"\nOverview.\nThe Dread Approach: After the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Empress%20Shek%27zeer\"&gt;Grand Empress Shek'zeer&lt;/a&gt;'s army is repelled during &lt;a href=\"The%20Wrath%20of%20Shek%27zeer\"&gt;The Wrath of Shek'zeer&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Klaxxi\"&gt;Klaxxi&lt;/a&gt;-aligned &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s venture into the Heart of Fear to finish the job. &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Vizier%20Zor%27lok\"&gt;Imperial Vizier Zor'lok&lt;/a&gt;, previously seen during &lt;a href=\"The%20Empress%27%20Gambit\"&gt;The Empress' Gambit&lt;/a&gt;, stands as the first boss, constantly spouting praise of his fear-driven empress and using powerful sonic magic. After silencing the zealot, the adventurers face off against &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Lord%20Ta%27yak\"&gt;Blade Lord Ta'yak&lt;/a&gt;, the mantid blademaster who wields great skill with both steel and wind magic. Progressing upward onto a great terrace, the mantid mages of wind summon &lt;a href=\"Garalon\"&gt;Garalon&lt;/a&gt;, mightiest of the mantid's &lt;a href=\"Kunchong\"&gt;Kunchong&lt;/a&gt;. Though it's carapace was mighty, the adventurers killed the beast by destroying it's legs to weaken it. \nThe Madness of Shek'zeer: Fearful of the coming threat, &lt;a href=\"Wind%20Lord%20Mel%27jarak\"&gt;Wind Lord Mel'jarak&lt;/a&gt; rallies the remaining elite mantid forces to guard the empress' inner sanctum. Slaying him, the final room before the throne room is a expanse of experiments of &lt;a href=\"Amber-Shaper%20Un%27sok\"&gt;Amber-Shaper Un'sok&lt;/a&gt;, chief scientist and former associate of &lt;a href=\"Xaril%20the%20Poisoned%20Mind\"&gt;Xaril the Poisoned Mind&lt;/a&gt;. The fearful mad scientist threw every experiment he had at the invaders before falling. During the final battle, the &lt;a href=\"Sha%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Sha of Fear&lt;/a&gt; empowers Shek'zeer, allowing her to use a combination of sonic and &lt;a href=\"sha\"&gt;sha&lt;/a&gt; magic. As she dies, the Sha of Fear escapes, later to be hunted down to the &lt;a href=\"Terrace%20of%20Endless%20Spring\"&gt;Terrace of Endless Spring&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Klaxxi\"&gt;Klaxxi&lt;/a&gt; presumably take up leadership until the next empress is born. \nQuest guide.\nAll bosses have a chance (on all difficulties) to drop &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20of%20Power\"&gt;Sigil of Power&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Sigil of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"The%20Strength%20of%20One%27s%20Foes\"&gt;The Strength of One's Foes&lt;/a&gt;.\nDungeon denizens.\nBosses.\n\"Spurred on by the Klaxxi, the time has come to assault the heart of the mantid empire.\"\n\"The mantid Empress, consumed by paranoia and twisted by the Sha of Fear, rules from her seat deep within the Heart of Fear.\"\nLoot.\nAll bosses have a chance to drop the &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20of%20Power\"&gt;Sigil of Power&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Sigil of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; in addition to the listed loot.\nVideos.\n&lt;vplayer /&gt;\nSpeculation.\nThe Heart of Fear might once have been &lt;a href=\"Manti%27vess\"&gt;Manti'vess&lt;/a&gt;."}
