{"id": "317958", "revid": "41425291", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=317958", "title": "Desolace storyline", "text": "\"This article is about the zone storyline after the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;. For the version, see &lt;a href=\"Desolace%20storyline%20%28Classic%29\"&gt;Desolace storyline (Classic)&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nDesolace is a level 30 - 35 zone in western &lt;a href=\"Kalimdor\"&gt;Kalimdor&lt;/a&gt; for both the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;. It starts out separated, with the Alliance going to &lt;a href=\"Nijel%27s%20Point\"&gt;Nijel's Point&lt;/a&gt; and the Horde going to &lt;a href=\"Furien%27s%20Post\"&gt;Furien's Post&lt;/a&gt;. After that, they both come together with quests offered at &lt;a href=\"Ethel%20Rethor\"&gt;Ethel Rethor&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Cenarion%20Wildlands\"&gt;Cenarion Wildlands&lt;/a&gt; before separating again with sending alliance to &lt;a href=\"Thargad%27s%20Camp\"&gt;Thargad's Camp&lt;/a&gt; and Horde players to &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Walker%20Post\"&gt;Ghost Walker Post&lt;/a&gt; on the fringes of the Wildlands and &lt;a href=\"Shadowprey%20Village\"&gt;Shadowprey Village&lt;/a&gt; on the southern coast.\nThe storyline is tracked in the quest &lt;a href=\"Desolace%20Quests\"&gt;Desolace Quests&lt;/a&gt;.\nFactional start.\nOn Behalf of the Horde.\n gives some other quests:\nThreats from Sar'theris Stand.\nUpon completion of \"My Word is Bond\", &lt;a href=\"Karnum%20Marshweaver\"&gt;Karnum Marshweaver&lt;/a&gt; offers his next quest:\nBizby.\nBizby is not required to complete the tracking achievement."}
{"id": "652993", "revid": "41423286", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=652993", "title": "Desolace storyline (Classic)", "text": "\"This article is about the zone storyline before the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;. For the live version, see &lt;a href=\"Desolace%20storyline\"&gt;Desolace storyline&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Desolace\"&gt;Desolace&lt;/a&gt; is questing zone (level range of 30-39) for both the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;. The main quest hub for the Alliance is located in &lt;a href=\"Nijel%27s%20Point\"&gt;Nijel's Point&lt;/a&gt;, whereas the Horde players can find quests both in &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Walker%20Post%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Ghost Walker Post&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadowprey%20Village\"&gt;Shadowprey Village&lt;/a&gt;. There are many neutral quests located in the zone as well, from greedy goblin business to centaur clan rivalry.\nAlliance storyline.\nCorporal Melkins sends the adventurer to collect 15 centaur ears from any clan in the region. According to him: \"each has its own leader and agenda, but all the clans have one thing in common: cruelty\".\nReclaimer's Inc.\n&lt;a href=\"Roetten%20Stonehammer\"&gt;Roetten Stonehammer&lt;/a&gt;, at the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Explorers\"&gt;Hall of Explorers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ironforge\"&gt;Ironforge&lt;/a&gt; has word that &lt;a href=\"Reclaimers%20Inc.\"&gt;Reclaimers Inc.&lt;/a&gt; work for someone, out in Desolace. He tells you to seek out &lt;a href=\"Kreldig%20Ungor\"&gt;Kreldig Ungor&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nijel%27s%20Point\"&gt;Nijel's Point&lt;/a&gt;. Learning that Roetten sent you, Kreldig welcomes the adventurer and compliments his choice of employment.\n\"This quest is also a prerequisite for \u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Karnitol%20Shipwreck\"&gt;The Karnitol Shipwreck&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Reagents%20for%20Reclaimers%20Inc.%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Reagents for Reclaimers Inc. (quest)&lt;/a&gt;, given by Kreldig.\"\nKreldig has a shopping list for &lt;a href=\"Leftwitch\"&gt;Leftwitch&lt;/a&gt;, a gnome mage in &lt;a href=\"Kharanos\"&gt;Kharanos&lt;/a&gt;. First on the list are horns and claws from the &lt;a href=\"Satyrs\"&gt;hatefury satyrs&lt;/a&gt;.\nSecond and third on Leftwitch's list are aged kodo hides, and scorpashi venom.\nKreldig sends the adventurer out one more time. This time, you're to bring back yet more demon parts. And nothing neat and clean like claws and horns, either. Leftwitch wants brains, wings, and blood. \nHaving done everything else to collect items for Leftwitch's order, Kreldig asks the adventurer to take the package back to &lt;a href=\"Roetten%20Stonehammer\"&gt;Roetten Stonehammer&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ironforge\"&gt;Ironforge&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Karnitol Shipwreck.\nOne of Kreldig's tasks is to recover a chest for a Stormwind mage named Karnitol. Apparently, his ship was attacked by sea giants, and his belongings were lost.\nAfter finding the empty chest at Ethel Rethor's coast, the adventurer returns to Kreldig for further instructions.\nKreldig suspects that Karnitol's satchel's might be in the ocean with a naga tribe, and he sends the adventurer to look for it there. \nVahlarriel's Search.\nVahlarriel is a night elf who is investigating the disappearrence of two missing nobles of a Darnassian merchant family: &lt;a href=\"Tyranis%20Malem\"&gt;Tyranis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dalinda%20Malem\"&gt;Dalinda&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"House%20Malem\"&gt;House Malem&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn his first quest, Vahlarriel asks the adventurer to investigate the whereabouts of &lt;a href=\"Tyranis%20Malem\"&gt;Tyranis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dalinda%20Malem\"&gt;Dalinda&lt;/a&gt;'s wagon, that was last seen near the road to &lt;a href=\"Stonetalon%20Mountains\"&gt;Stonetalon Mountains&lt;/a&gt;\nAfter finding the destroyed wagon without any corpses, the adventurer returns to Vahlarriel to report his findings. Vahlarriel's suspects that the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Blade%20clan\"&gt;Burning Blade&lt;/a&gt; might have captured both to &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Axe%20Fortress\"&gt;Thunder Axe Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nVahlarriel informs the adventurer that it is more important to find Dalinda, leaving hints of some suspicion on Tyranis intentions in coming to Desolace.\nVenturing into &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Axe%20Fortress\"&gt;Thunder Axe Fortress&lt;/a&gt; the adventurer finds &lt;a href=\"Dalinda%20Malem\"&gt;Dalinda&lt;/a&gt; alive, and she informs about the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Blade%20clan\"&gt;Burning Blade's&lt;/a&gt; plans to sacrife her for their demon masters. She them asks the adventurer to find her brother, who, according to her, had recently begun craving for arcane knowledge. The adventurer finds &lt;a href=\"Tyranis%20Malem\"&gt;Tyranis&lt;/a&gt; in a corrupted state, alligned with other &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Blade%20clan\"&gt;Burning Blade&lt;/a&gt; members, and kills him. In the end of the quest, the adventurer hands &lt;a href=\"Tyranis%20Malem\"&gt;Tyranis&lt;/a&gt;' necklace to his sister and explains about his corruption.\nFinally, the adventurer escorts &lt;a href=\"Dalinda%20Malem\"&gt;Dalinda&lt;/a&gt; out of &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Axe%20Fortress\"&gt;Thunder Axe Fortress&lt;/a&gt;, and them returns to Vahlarriel to conclude his mission.\nOther quests.\nThis quest is part of a chain that starts in &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Stormwind's Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Brother%20Crowley\"&gt;Brother Crowley&lt;/a&gt;. Crowley sends the adventurer to meet &lt;a href=\"Brother%20Anton\"&gt;Brother Anton&lt;/a&gt;, a member of the Scarlet Crusade situated in &lt;a href=\"Nijel%27s%20Point\"&gt;Nijel's Point&lt;/a&gt; to investigate the undead presence in the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Bones\"&gt;Valley of Bones&lt;/a&gt;. After killing some skeletons for Anton, the adventurer receives a recommendation letter and is sent to Southshore to continue his efforts against the undead.\nHorde storyline.\nGhost Walker Post.\nAlliance relations.\nThis quest chain starts in &lt;a href=\"Orgrimmar\"&gt;Orgrimmar&lt;/a&gt;, but is mainly done in &lt;a href=\"Desolace\"&gt;Desolace&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe corrupter.\nThis chain can be started by acquiring a &lt;a href=\"Flayed%20Demon%20Skin\"&gt;Flayed Demon Skin&lt;/a&gt;, dropped in &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Axe%20Fortress\"&gt;Thunder Axe Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe adventurer can retrieve the demon skin to &lt;a href=\"Maurin%20Bonesplitter\"&gt;Maurin Bonesplitter&lt;/a&gt; in Ghost Walker Post to uncover the nature of some mysterious red markings in it. &lt;a href=\"Maurin%20Bonesplitter\"&gt;Maurin&lt;/a&gt; explains that it is a demonic language similar to the Eredun language, and he recognizes a demon signature from &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Azrethoc\"&gt;Lord Azrethoc&lt;/a&gt;. Apparently, this is the main demon guiding the Burning Blade's activity in the area.\nMaurin requests a scalp from a specific type of satyr in Desolace: the &lt;a href=\"Hatefury%20Shadowstalker\"&gt;hatefury shadowstalker&lt;/a&gt;. He explains that it will work as a reagent to find &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Azrethoc\"&gt;Lord Azrethoc&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfterwards, Maurin requests the next reagent: a &lt;a href=\"Oracle%20Crystal\"&gt;Oracle Crystal&lt;/a&gt; from the local &lt;a href=\"Desolace\"&gt;Desolace&lt;/a&gt; naga. At the end of the quest, Maurin is able to summon a vision of a Burning Blade warlock (Jugkar Grim'rod) and his master: &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Azrethoc\"&gt;Lord Azrethoc&lt;/a&gt;.\nMaurin instructs the adventurer to talk to Takata Steelblade, an orc blademaster in Ghost Walker Post, in order to prepare for the confrontation against the demon.\nIn the final part of this chain, &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Azrethoc\"&gt;Lord Azrethoc&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jugkar%20Grim%27rod\"&gt;Jugkar Grim'rod&lt;/a&gt; are defeated in &lt;a href=\"Mannoroc%20Coven\"&gt;Mannoroc Coven&lt;/a&gt;.\nNeutral.\nGoblin quests.\nThe goblin Smeed is interested in taming some kodos with his kodo kombulator: a device that rejuvenates and tames aged kodo.\nThe Gizelton brothers are goblins caravan travelers that roam through Desolace. In two distinct spots, they offer a quest for adventurer's willing to aid the protection of their kodo caravan.\nThe goblin &lt;a href=\"Hornizz%20Brimbuzzle\"&gt;Hornizz Brimbuzzle&lt;/a&gt; is looking for adventures willing to collect some ghost energy with his ghost-o-plasm magnet. For this purpose, he directs the adventurer to the Valley of Bones, where Magram ghosts reside.\nApparently kodo bones are valuable trade items, and Bibbly F'utzbuckle needs some help collecting them. She wants to sell them to a caravan that often resell them at &lt;a href=\"Shadowprey%20Village\"&gt;Shadowprey Village&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Melizza%20Brimbuzzle\"&gt;Melizza Brimbuzzle&lt;/a&gt; can be found trapped by the Maraudine centaur in the Valley of Spears. She came to do business with them, but they were more interested in cooking her. The adventurer can free her and grab a reward with her brother, &lt;a href=\"Hornizz%20Brimbuzzle\"&gt;Hornizz Brimbuzzle&lt;/a&gt;.\nEthel Rethor.\nAzore Aldamort.\n&lt;a href=\"Azore%20Aldamort\"&gt;Azore Aldamort&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn\"&gt;Argent Dawn&lt;/a&gt; archmage interested in recovering artifacts in &lt;a href=\"Desolace\"&gt;Desolace&lt;/a&gt;. In his first quest, he asks the adventurer to venture the Burning Blade's Thunder Axe Fortress to recover a naga magical weapon: the Sceptre of Light.\nOn his second quest, Aldamort trusts the adventurer the posession of the &lt;a href=\"Gem%20of%20the%20Serpent\"&gt;Gem of the Serpent&lt;/a&gt;] to summon the naga who is protecting the Book of the Ancients, a tome that he wants to pass over to the Argent Dawn's council protection.\nUlysses Rackmore.\nThe adventurer can find Ulysses Rackmore's &lt;a href=\"Rackmore%27s%20Log\"&gt;logbook&lt;/a&gt; along the coast of Ethel Rethor, in which we will describe how to open his chest in &lt;a href=\"Ranazjar%20Isle\"&gt;Ranazjar Isle&lt;/a&gt;. In order to do so, it is required a golden and a silver key, which can be dropped from local makrura and naga.\nCentaur quests.\nThe adventurer can decide which centaur clan he will be alligned to in Desolace: the Gelkis (&lt;a href=\"Strange%20Alliance\"&gt;Strange Alliance&lt;/a&gt; &amp; &lt;a href=\"Gelkis%20Alliance\"&gt;Gelkis Alliance&lt;/a&gt;) or the Magram (&lt;a href=\"Brutal%20Politics\"&gt;Brutal Politics&lt;/a&gt; &amp; &lt;a href=\"Magram%20Alliance\"&gt;Magram Alliance&lt;/a&gt;). Starting those quests, in either Nijel's Point or Ghost Walker Post, adventurer's will unlock more quests to gain more reputation with their preffered clan.\nGelkis.\nAfter hearing whispers of the adventurer's name, the Uthek requests ten &lt;a href=\"Crude%20Charm\"&gt;crude charm&lt;/a&gt; from the Kolkar Clan.\nIn his next mission, Uthek wants to steal some supplies from the &lt;a href=\"Magram%20clan\"&gt;Magram Clan&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfterwards, &lt;a href=\"Uthek%20the%20Wise\"&gt;Uthek&lt;/a&gt; requests the adventurer to travel to the &lt;a href=\"Swamp%20of%20Sorrows\"&gt;Swamp of Sorrows&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Kingdoms\"&gt;Eastern Kingdoms&lt;/a&gt; in order to retrieve a &lt;a href=\"Draenethyst%20Crystal\"&gt;draenethyst crystal&lt;/a&gt; from a &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Draenei\"&gt;broken draenei&lt;/a&gt; called &lt;a href=\"Ongeku\"&gt;Ongeku&lt;/a&gt;."}
