{"id": "504367", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=504367", "title": "Destiny Unfulfilled", "text": "Objectives.\nWitness True Betrayal in Shadowmoon Valley on the fringes of Outland.\nDescription.\nHardly recognizable from the golden eyed child of prophecy, and living as an outcast on the fringes of a shattered world, his motivation remained unchanged. His assaults on the Legion and his attempts to end their march were his only focus.\nYet, in a strange twist of fate, it was not the Burning Legion who came for him in the end.\nWe must travel to Outland to experience Illidan's last memory.\nRewards.\nYou will also receive:\nCompletion.\nDemon hunters.\nForgive me, noble soul. I mislead you. Light's Heart was not the vessel that required preparation, it was yours.\nYou, who sacrificed everything for your world, and served your master dutifully until the end. These memories will serve to strengthen your resolve. Look to them when the dark temptation surrounds you and let them grant you the strength to resist and rise against the corrupters.\nWe will save Illidan and once more you will battle at the side of your master for the fate of all worlds.\nPlayers who have killed Illidan.\nI wept when I touched your consciousness in the Great Dark, mortal. For I saw his fall, and I saw you, your shadow casting a dark pall over his body. I felt hatred in your heart as it corrupted your mind.\nIt was not Light's Heart, but you, that needed preparation. Now you know truth. Are you prepared to do what must be done to save your world and all others?\nWhen the time is right, I will call upon you to begin the hunt for Illidan's soul.\nHis rebirth will be the story of your redemption.\nPlayers who have not killed Illidan.\nIn the end, the denizens of Azeroth and Outland came to exact their vengeance upon Illidan. Though you did not strike a blow against him, you were complicit in his fall.\nI showed you Illidan's life so that you would understand why h