{"id": "69804", "revid": "40286693", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=69804", "title": "Destroyer", "text": "Destroyers are intermediary &lt;a href=\"warship\"&gt;warship&lt;/a&gt;s intended to fight during naval engagements as well as escort other vessels like &lt;a href=\"transport%20ship\"&gt;transport ship&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"battleship\"&gt;battleship&lt;/a&gt;s. Many of the races of &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt; and have their own variant of the destroyer class.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;commanders&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Lunarfall\"&gt;Lunarfall&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Frostwall\"&gt;Frostwall&lt;/a&gt; can also build at their garrison &lt;a href=\"shipyard\"&gt;shipyard&lt;/a&gt;. They are good against &lt;a href=\"submarine\"&gt;submarine&lt;/a&gt;s and weak against &lt;a href=\"battleship\"&gt;battleship&lt;/a&gt;s.\nElven destroyer.\nSecond War.\nElven destroyers were powerful warships from the fleets of &lt;a href=\"Quel%27Thalas%20%28kingdom%29\"&gt;Quel'Thalas&lt;/a&gt;. Crewed with highly-skilled &lt;a href=\"High%20elf\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; seafarers, these swift-sailing vessels were prepared to engage the enemy wherever they might be found. Elven destroyers constituted a critical part of the &lt;a href=\"Alliance%20of%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; naval defense force as they could unleash their firepower upon dreaded aerial forces of the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt;.\nWorld of Warcraft.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Blood%20elf\"&gt;blood elves&lt;/a&gt; later reclaimed a few destroyers, the ones that were reclaimed receiving new red sails instead of the classical blue with a &lt;a href=\"unicorn\"&gt;unicorn&lt;/a&gt; image.\nElven destroyers of the trireme hull type employ \"junk sails\" in a \"schooner rig\". This sail configuration is characterized by good windward handling and generally good speed across all sailing points (but less from running with the wind). This is consistent with the idea that the elven destroyer is a fast, highly maneuverable warship.\nMany ruined older elven destroyers could be found in \"&lt;a href=\"World%20of%20Warcraft\"&gt;World of Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\". With \"\", an intact blood elven destroyer could be found anchored in &lt;a href=\"Sunsail%20Anchorage\"&gt;Sunsail Anchorage&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Eversong%20Woods\"&gt;Eversong Woods&lt;/a&gt;, amidst the wreckage of the high elven destroyers of old. More and more ships were then added later.\nNotable elven destroyers.\n&lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;:\nTroll destroyer.\nSecond War.\nThe troll destroyers (also known as wave riders) were swift, ill-visaged longboats designed to cut through enemy armadas and deal damage to enemy vessels and their flying support. The savage &lt;a href=\"Forest%20troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; crewmen were eager to enter into combat against &lt;a href=\"Alliance%20of%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; ships of war and hungrily awaited any chance to stand mast to mast against the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Destroyer%20%28Warcraft%20II%29\"&gt;elven destroyers&lt;/a&gt;.\nWorld of Warcraft.\nSmall canoe-like troll ships appear in ' and ', seemingly inspired by them, but much smaller and unarmed. Large ships belonging to &lt;a href=\"Zul\"&gt;Zul&lt;/a&gt;'s war fleet seen at &lt;a href=\"Stormsea%20Landing\"&gt;Stormsea Landing&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Giants\"&gt;Isle of Giants&lt;/a&gt; seem to be based on a similar design, though mainly built for transport. The &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Fleet\"&gt;Golden Fleet&lt;/a&gt; has both troll destroyers and troll &lt;a href=\"battleship\"&gt;battleship&lt;/a&gt;s.\nHuman destroyer.\nHuman destroyers (also known as icebreakers) are massive paddlewheel-driven behemoths functioning on steam power and originally built to get through the icy waters of &lt;a href=\"Northrend\"&gt;Northrend&lt;/a&gt;. To accomplish this they have a ram similar to a &lt;a href=\"battleship\"&gt;battleship&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey can be seen at &lt;a href=\"Menethil%20Harbor\"&gt;Menethil Harbor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20Harbor\"&gt;Stormwind Harbor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Valgarde\"&gt;Valgarde&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Valiance%20Keep\"&gt;Valiance Keep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Venture%20Bay\"&gt;Venture Bay&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Strand%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;Strand of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Conquest\"&gt;Isle of Conquest&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Highbank\"&gt;Highbank&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is possible that the steam powerplant and paddlewheel system for these ships had, at the very least, &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Gnome\"&gt;gnomish&lt;/a&gt; technical expertise in their design, as both races have considerable experience with steam power.\nEarly in development, they were previously reported to be called \"steamships\".\nNotable human destroyers.\n&lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;:\n, Alliance:\nOrc destroyer.\nOrc destroyers are small spiked craft. These ships have also been called \"gunships\", though that name normally refers to the &lt;a href=\"Gunship\"&gt;flying crafts&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Wayward%20Landing\"&gt;Wayward Landing&lt;/a&gt; was an area, removed from the beta stage of \"Mists of Pandaria\", that was under attack by Horde forces led by &lt;a href=\"Grothok%20Blackcrag\"&gt;Grothok Blackcrag&lt;/a&gt;, who had the title \"Destroyer Captain\".\nNotable orc destroyers.\n&lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;:\n, Horde:\n, Iron Horde:\n, pirates:\nArakkoa destroyer.\nThe &lt;a href=\"arakkoa\"&gt;arakkoa&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Awakened\"&gt;Order of the Awakened&lt;/a&gt; were known to have at least a destroyer, \"\". It was a powerful ship with large &lt;a href=\"cannon\"&gt;cannon&lt;/a&gt;s, able to counter both &lt;a href=\"submarine\"&gt;submarine&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"battleship\"&gt;battleship&lt;/a&gt;s. Both Alliance and Horde &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;commanders&lt;/a&gt; could buy its allegiance.\nIn the RPG.\nElven destroyers are heavy, iron-clad &lt;a href=\"warship\"&gt;warship&lt;/a&gt;s that can quickly carry a half-dozen heavy &lt;a href=\"cannon\"&gt;cannon&lt;/a&gt; to any point on a coastline and bombard a target into submission. The destroyer moves at 20 miles per hour and has a crew of 7 (1 pilot and 6 gunners)."}
