{"id": "244523", "revid": "40286693", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=244523", "title": "1st Legion", "text": "The 1st Legion (or the Expeditionary Forces) was the name of the &lt;a href=\"Alliance%20of%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; military forces who accompanied &lt;a href=\"Arthas%20Menethil\"&gt;Prince Arthas&lt;/a&gt; in his quest to &lt;a href=\"Northrend\"&gt;Northrend&lt;/a&gt; to destroy the &lt;a href=\"nathrezim\"&gt;nathrezim&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mal%27Ganis\"&gt;Mal'Ganis&lt;/a&gt;. They were ultimately betrayed and slain by Arthas before being raised as &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;. Some of their ghosts are still haunting their original landing zone at the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Shore%20%28Dragonblight%29\"&gt;Forgotten Shore&lt;/a&gt; and the souls of yet more members were once trapped in &lt;a href=\"Frostmourne\"&gt;Frostmourne&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThird War.\nThe Expeditionary Forces came to &lt;a href=\"Northrend\"&gt;Northrend&lt;/a&gt; under the command of &lt;a href=\"Arthas%20Menethil\"&gt;Prince Arthas&lt;/a&gt; in order to combat the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Scourge\"&gt;Undead Scourge&lt;/a&gt; and slay the &lt;a href=\"dreadlord\"&gt;dreadlord&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mal%27Ganis\"&gt;Mal'Ganis&lt;/a&gt;. Soon after arriving in Northrend they met up with &lt;a href=\"Muradin%20Bronzebeard\"&gt;Muradin Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Expedition\"&gt;his expedition&lt;/a&gt; and the forces united with one another. In time an &lt;a href=\"Alliance%20Emissary\"&gt;Emissary&lt;/a&gt; arrived from &lt;a href=\"Terenas%20Menethil\"&gt;King Terenas&lt;/a&gt; who ordered the expedition to return to &lt;a href=\"Lordaeron\"&gt;Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt;, after &lt;a href=\"Uther%20the%20Lightbringer\"&gt;Lord Uther&lt;/a&gt; had persuaded him to do so. &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Luc%20Valonforth\"&gt;Captain Luc Valonforth&lt;/a&gt;, in order to avoid the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;, ordered the expedition forces to cut their way through the woods in order to reach their ships. As the men began chopping their way through the words Captain Valonforth enlightened the Prince to their new orders. Knowing that he needed his men in order to slay Mal'Ganis, Arthas and a reluctant Muradin ventured forth to burn the ships in order to keep the men by his side. By the time the expeditionary forces finished cutting through the forest, the last of their ships were burning and with Prince Arthas before them. Arthas quickly blamed the mercenaries (who he had hired) for burning the ships and led the expeditionary forces against them himself.\nAfter that, the First Legion accompanied Arthas to defeat Mal'Ganis. Arthas and Muradin went with a group to obtain the runesword &lt;a href=\"Frostmourne\"&gt;Frostmourne&lt;/a&gt;, Arthas returned with the bad news that Muradin died, but that they were able to obtain the sword.\nAfter Arthas finally destroyed the dreadlord, the prince along with Froustmourne disappeared into the frozen wastes, leaving the First Legion stranded in Northrend; during that wait, food was scarce and the cold was fierce; In the midst of that, the dwarf &lt;a href=\"Baelgun%20Flamebeard\"&gt;Baelgun Flamebeard&lt;/a&gt; took command of the original expedition of Muradin's dwarves and they parted ways with the 1st Legion and subsequently venturing into the broken kingdom of Azjol-Nerub.\nCaptain Falric went to find Arthas but did not return. Arthas slaughtered him and turned him into a death knight. Afterward, &lt;a href=\"Falric\"&gt;Falric&lt;/a&gt; slaughtered &lt;a href=\"Thassarian\"&gt;Thassarian&lt;/a&gt;, and subsequently Arthas wiped out the majority of the First Legion. Apparently continuing without their leader, the 1st Legion forces made it to Icecrown after their prince became a death knight, and it was there that they met their end. Two soldiers, &lt;a href=\"Orik%20Trueheart\"&gt;Orik Trueheart&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"William%20Allerton\"&gt;William Allerton&lt;/a&gt;, managed to escape.\nAfterward, &lt;a href=\"Valgarde\"&gt;Valgarde&lt;/a&gt; became the first home of the lucky few who survived Arthas' betrayal.\nWrath of the Lich King.\nAt the time of the &lt;a href=\"war%20against%20the%20Lich%20King\"&gt;war against the Lich King&lt;/a&gt;, Orik and William joined different forces and traveled once more to Northrend. Orik returned to the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Shore%20%28Dragonblight%29\"&gt;Forgotten Shore&lt;/a&gt;, which had been the base of the First Legion during the Third War. Several souls of soldiers from the First Legion who accompanied Arthas in the past were found on the coast, these souls did not seem to know of Arthas' betrayal. Orik enlisted the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;'s help to free the souls from their torment.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Reflection\"&gt;Halls of Reflection&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Icecrown%20Citadel\"&gt;Icecrown Citadel&lt;/a&gt;, the heroes had to face the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt;s of members of the 1st Legion.\nIn the RPG.\n&lt;a href=\"Apothecary%20Oni%27jus\"&gt;Oni'jus&lt;/a&gt; was one of Prince Arthas' infiltrators before the &lt;a href=\"Third%20War\"&gt;Third War&lt;/a&gt;.\nVideos.\n&lt;vplayer/&gt;"}
