{"id": "19148", "revid": "55745224", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19148", "title": "Razormane tribe", "text": "The Razormane tribe is a &lt;a href=\"tribe\"&gt;tribe&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"quilboar\"&gt;quilboar&lt;/a&gt; that inhabit &lt;a href=\"Durotar\"&gt;Durotar&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Barrens\"&gt;Barrens&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Razormane led by &lt;a href=\"Nak\"&gt;Nak&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kuz\"&gt;Kuz&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lok%20Orcbane\"&gt;Lok Orcbane&lt;/a&gt; have been known to raid the &lt;a href=\"Crossroads\"&gt;Crossroads&lt;/a&gt; and steal supplies. They were at war with the &lt;a href=\"Bristleback%20tribe\"&gt;Bristleback&lt;/a&gt; quilboars.\nAt some point in the past, when the mysterious &lt;a href=\"Kelani%20Magi\"&gt;kelani magi&lt;/a&gt; fell, the Razormane quilboar were quick to scavenge their &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20Gemstone\"&gt;Enchanted Gemstone&lt;/a&gt;s.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt; split the Barrens, the Razormanes were thrown into chaos. The northern group became &lt;a href=\"refugee\"&gt;refugee&lt;/a&gt;s separated from their leadership, until they rallied under &lt;a href=\"Tortusk\"&gt;Tortusk&lt;/a&gt;, who turned them into brigands and had them attack &lt;a href=\"Grol%27dom%20Farm\"&gt;Grol'dom Farm&lt;/a&gt;. After his death, the orcs thought about starting a dialogue with the survivors.\nLocations.\nThe Razormane inhabit mostly the area around &lt;a href=\"Thorn%20Hill\"&gt;Thorn Hill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blackthorn%20Ridge\"&gt;Blackthorn Ridge&lt;/a&gt; (bordering the &lt;a href=\"Razorfen%20tribe\"&gt;Razorfen tribe&lt;/a&gt; to the south), and expand into the &lt;a href=\"Razormane%20Grounds\"&gt;Razormane Grounds&lt;/a&gt; in search of new land in the orc territory of &lt;a href=\"Durotar\"&gt;Durotar&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Zekhan\"&gt;Zekhan&lt;/a&gt; reported that there is a &lt;a href=\"Razormane%20Downs\"&gt;Razormane Downs&lt;/a&gt; somewhere in southern Durotar.\nCulture.\nThe Razormane quilboar are a spiritual tribe. They know that their bones need to be strong when entering a battle, with the Razormane's greatest warriors being infused with Agamaggan's strength. The Razormane's greatest scouts are said to be unrivaled in their accuracy, and no rogue could measure up to their quickness in battle.\n&lt;a href=\"Tortusk\"&gt;Tortusk&lt;/a&gt;'s mount is a &lt;a href=\"raptor\"&gt;raptor&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Fez\"&gt;Fez&lt;/a&gt;.\nTypes.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Warcraft%20III\"&gt;Warcraft III&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn Warcraft III you must help the tauren defeat the Razormane quilboar who are invading their home.\nIn the RPG.\nRazormanes are one of the two most prominent quilboar tribes. Native to the Barrens, they frequently raid and pillage nearby settlements.\nSpeculation.\nIt's possible Mangletooth has been the leader of the tribe since the beginning, leading heroes of the Horde to believe that Lok Orcbane was the leader. This way Mangletooth could have his vengeance on them for leaving him captured at &lt;a href=\"Camp%20Taurajo\"&gt;Camp Taurajo&lt;/a&gt;. Even when Mangletooth has the adventurer bring the skull of Lok as proof of the leader's death, &lt;a href=\"Thork\"&gt;Thork&lt;/a&gt; thought the leader was a different quilboar.\nIt's also possible, given how the quilboar take over new leadership, that Mangletooth was the chieftain and challenged by Lok who won, leaving Mangletooth for dead. Lok then would have taken over the tribe, leaving Mangletooth wanting revenge.\nThis could explain how quickly and easily Mangletooth was able to become the chieftain of the tribe after having either escape or released from Camp Taurajo."}
{"id": "80508", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=80508", "title": "Razormaw", "text": "Razormaw is an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"black%20dragon\"&gt;black dragon&lt;/a&gt; that haunts &lt;a href=\"Wyrmscar%20Island\"&gt;Wyrmscar Island&lt;/a&gt; off the coast of &lt;a href=\"Bloodmyst%20Isle\"&gt;Bloodmyst Isle&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is summoned by using the &lt;a href=\"Bundle%20of%20Dragon%20Bones\"&gt;Bundle of Dragon Bones&lt;/a&gt;, provided by &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Toreth\"&gt;Prince Toreth&lt;/a&gt;, on the &lt;a href=\"Ever-burning%20Pyre\"&gt;Ever-burning Pyre&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nRazormaw is a former lieutenant of &lt;a href=\"Deathwing\"&gt;Deathwing&lt;/a&gt;. Many thousands of years before the present time, the night elves of &lt;a href=\"Silvergale%20Isle\"&gt;Silvergale Isle&lt;/a&gt; made a pact with the Aspect &lt;a href=\"Ysera\"&gt;Ysera&lt;/a&gt;'s brood. The elves were gifted with Ysera's blessing and were allowed to ride the &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt;s into battle against their enemies. They were known as the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Riders%20of%20Loreth%27Aran\"&gt;Dragon Riders of Loreth'Aran&lt;/a&gt;. This unfortunately attracted &lt;a href=\"Deathwing\"&gt;Deathwing&lt;/a&gt;'s ire, and he sent his flight, including his lieutenant Razormaw, to launch an attack on the night elves while they were sleeping. The &lt;a href=\"green%20dragonflight\"&gt;green dragons&lt;/a&gt; rose up to protect their elven allies but eventually they were all defeated by Deathwing's brood. Razormaw however, also perished in the final battle.\nMany thousands of years later the remains of battle can still be seen. Gigantic draconic skeletons litter the isle and the spirits of green whelps wander aimlessly, attacking all that approach. Razormaw's hatred was so great that even in death he still remains, as a spectral dragon circling overhead. Prince Toreth, a ghost of one of the riders that remains to keep the world from forgetting the Dragon Riders of Loreth'Aran, asks passing adventurers to summon down the ghostly black dragon, and defeat it to end the haunting of the isle."}
{"id": "120787", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=120787", "title": "Razormaw (quest)", "text": "Objectives.\n&lt;a href=\"Prince%20Toreth\"&gt;Prince Toreth&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Wyrmscar%20Island\"&gt;Wyrmscar Island&lt;/a&gt; has asked that you slay &lt;a href=\"Razormaw\"&gt;Razormaw&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nMany of the &lt;a href=\"black%20dragonflight\"&gt;black dragonflight&lt;/a&gt; were slain during the attacks. One of them, a lieutenant of &lt;a href=\"Deathwing\"&gt;Deathwing&lt;/a&gt; himself, still haunts this place. If you look to the heavens, you can see his spectral countenance circling the skies. His hatred is so great that he remains even in death.\nTake the bones that you gathered for me earlier to the top of the mountain on this island and place them in the &lt;a href=\"Ever-burning%20Pyre\"&gt;ever-burning pyre&lt;/a&gt;. This act should signal &lt;a href=\"Razormaw\"&gt;Razormaw&lt;/a&gt; to descend. When he does, slay his undead form.\nRewards.\nYou will also receive:\nProgress.\nI recommend that you bring allies, &lt;name&gt;.\nCompletion.\nHow long has it been? A thousand years? Ten-thousand perhaps? You have done me and the memory of my people a great service, &lt;name&gt;. Please accept this item of power as a token of appreciation from &lt;a href=\"Loreth%27Aran\"&gt;Loreth'Aran&lt;/a&gt; - in honor of your deeds. "}
