{"id": "45958", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45958", "title": "Lightning's Blade clan", "text": "The Lightning's Blade clan was an &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; clan that dwelled in northeastern &lt;a href=\"Blade%27s%20Edge%20Mountains\"&gt;Gorgrond&lt;/a&gt;. It had strong ties to the &lt;a href=\"Thunderlord%20clan\"&gt;Thunderlord clan&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; had conquered much of &lt;a href=\"Draenor\"&gt;Draenor&lt;/a&gt;, the threat of starvation caused many orcs to turn on each other, clashing in short-lived battles that left hundreds dead. The Lightning's Blade was one of the clans who suffered greatly in these conflicts. When the Horde &lt;a href=\"First%20War\"&gt;invaded&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;, the Lightning's Blade were left behind on Draenor. After the war, &lt;a href=\"Ner%27zhul\"&gt;Ner'zhul&lt;/a&gt; attempted to &lt;a href=\"Horde%20of%20Draenor\"&gt;reforge the Horde&lt;/a&gt; with a promise of new worlds, and managed to attain the partial loyalty of the Lightning's Blade. \nWarcraft Adventures: Lord of the Clans.\nIn the canceled \"\", &lt;a href=\"Zul%27jin\"&gt;Zul'jin&lt;/a&gt; had a banner of the clan inside his shop. The banner displayed a lightning and an axe crossed over a blue background. Zul'jin referred to the clan as ill-fated, and never making it to &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;. He heard their initiation rites were so harsh, few were ever able to pass them.\nAccording to Zul'jin, in those rites, young warriors were forced to stand on top of the highest peak of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%27s%20Edge%20Mountains\"&gt;Blade's Edge Mountains&lt;/a&gt; and hold aloft their axes during the thunderstorm. Only those struck by lightning at least three times could join the clan.\nSpeculation.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Sons\"&gt;Lightning Sons&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Garadar\"&gt;Garadar&lt;/a&gt; could be all that remains of the Lightning's Blade clan, and judging from their age, they could have formerly been &lt;a href=\"far%20seer\"&gt;far seer&lt;/a&gt;s of the clan."}
