{"id": "512594", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=512594", "title": "Lightspawn", "text": "Lightspawn are &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; creatures born of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;. \nEncountered only recently, they appear to be the Light's counterpart to &lt;a href=\"voidwalker\"&gt;voidwalker&lt;/a&gt;s, and can always be found amongst the battlefields of the Light. At least one was seen to have acted on its own to attempt to stop a necromantic ritual on &lt;a href=\"Exile%27s%20Reach\"&gt;Exile's Reach&lt;/a&gt; but was captured instead. After a new &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; freed it, it left &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;. A handful of others can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Netherlight%20Temple\"&gt;Netherlight Temple&lt;/a&gt;, order hall of the &lt;a href=\"Conclave\"&gt;Conclave&lt;/a&gt;, but also in &lt;a href=\"Revendreth\"&gt;Revendreth&lt;/a&gt; at the site of the Light's assault upon the realm: the &lt;a href=\"Ember%20Ward\"&gt;Ember Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nSimilar to other cosmic forces, Lightspawn can normally only be permanently killed in the realm of Light. If killed in the mortal realm, their essence returns to the Light to reconstitute, though some exceptionally powerful forces can intervene in the process."}
