{"id": "26080", "revid": "40380650", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26080", "title": "Silithid larva", "text": "Silithid larvae, also known as broodlings, are young &lt;a href=\"silithid\"&gt;silithid&lt;/a&gt; that as of yet been specialized for any role in the hive. Eventually the broodling encases itself in a cocoon and changes into its new form, such as a &lt;a href=\"silithid%20wasp\"&gt;wasp&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"silithid%20reaver\"&gt;reaver&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"silithid%20swarmer\"&gt;swarmer&lt;/a&gt;, or possibly any type of silithid found useful to the hive.\nNotes.\nThey can be found in the larger &lt;a href=\"Silithid%23Hives\"&gt;silithid hives&lt;/a&gt; in their chrysalis form. They cannot be targeted or attacked, and are essentially decoration."}
{"id": "26087", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26087", "title": "Silithid light", "text": "The silithid lights can be found in every hive or underground cave of the &lt;a href=\"silithid\"&gt;silithid&lt;/a&gt;. They are able to produce light to illuminate the dark caves.\nThese silithid lights could be thought of as larvae of the silithid considering these creatures are insect-like in their being. Just as a &lt;a href=\"firefly\"&gt;firefly&lt;/a&gt; produces a sort of glow, these youngling silithid may be the primary source of light in their deep caverns.\nThe &lt;a href=\"mantid\"&gt;mantid&lt;/a&gt; have similar mantis-creatures in the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Heart of Fear&lt;/a&gt;."}
