{"id": "126910", "revid": "28055547", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=126910", "title": "Silithus storyline", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Silithus\"&gt;Silithus&lt;/a&gt; is a contested level 55-60 zone in southwestern &lt;a href=\"Kalimdor\"&gt;Kalimdor&lt;/a&gt;. Most of the story is revolving around the rising activity of the &lt;a href=\"silithid\"&gt;silithid&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Twilight%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;Twilight's Hammer&lt;/a&gt; in the area, and will lead adventurers that arrive to &lt;a href=\"Cenarion%20Hold\"&gt;Cenarion Hold&lt;/a&gt; to deal with these threats.\nUnlike most other &lt;a href=\"old%20world\"&gt;old world&lt;/a&gt; zones, Silithus was not revamped in \"\" and has relatively few quests, especially compared to the other level 55-60 zone, &lt;a href=\"Blasted%20Lands\"&gt;Blasted Lands&lt;/a&gt;. For this reason, the area provides easy acces to Blasted Lands.\nThe progression of the storyline is tracked in the achievement &lt;a href=\"Silithus%20Quests\"&gt;Silithus Quests&lt;/a&gt;.\nCenarion Hold.\nWanted poster\nSaving Noggle quest chain\nTwilight Geolords quest chain\nThe following chains unlock after completion of Twilight Geolords chain:\nHive'Regal quest chain\nHermit Ortell quest chain"}
{"id": "58927", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=58927", "title": "Silithyst", "text": "Silithyst is \"strange red crystalline &lt;a href=\"dust\"&gt;dust&lt;/a&gt;\" that appears in the &lt;a href=\"Silithus\"&gt;Silithus&lt;/a&gt; desert, which both the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; would like to assemble in quantities as large as possible for researching purposes. Doing just that is the objective of the &lt;a href=\"world%20PvP\"&gt;world PvP&lt;/a&gt; event \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Silithyst%20Must%20Flow\"&gt;The Silithyst Must Flow&lt;/a&gt;\" and the world quest &lt;a href=\"Silithyst%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Silithyst (quest)&lt;/a&gt;, available during the &lt;a href=\"Call%20of%20the%20Scarab\"&gt;Call of the Scarab&lt;/a&gt; micro-holiday.\nCollecting Silithyst will result in a debuff that slows the character's speed considerably."}
{"id": "500577", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=500577", "title": "Silithyst (quest)", "text": "Silithyst is a PvP world quest, serving as a callback to &lt;a href=\"The%20Silithyst%20Must%20Flow\"&gt;The Silithyst Must Flow&lt;/a&gt;, added in &lt;a href=\"Patch%201.12\"&gt;Patch 1.12&lt;/a&gt;.\nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nNotes and guide.\nSilithyst spawns in an area centered on on both sides of the road southwest of the &lt;a href=\"Bones%20of%20Grakkarond\"&gt;Bones of Grakkarond&lt;/a&gt;. Interacting with a &lt;a href=\"Silithyst%20Geyser\"&gt;Silithyst Geyser&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Silithyst%20Mound\"&gt;Silithyst Mound&lt;/a&gt; will immediately flag the player for PvP. While carrying the dust, players are treated much like they were a flag carrier in &lt;a href=\"Capture%20the%20Flag\"&gt;Capture the Flag&lt;/a&gt; modes of PvP: mounting, gaining stealth or invulnerability will cause the player to drop the dust. Additionally, any run speed-enhancing abilities will not work as well.\nRun on foot to the collection point. The Alliance turn-in point is to the northwest, at on the edge of &lt;a href=\"Hive%27Zora\"&gt;Hive'Zora&lt;/a&gt;, while the Horde camp is off to the southeast at on the edge of &lt;a href=\"Hive%27Regal\"&gt;Hive'Regal&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "173899", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173899", "title": "Silithyst Geyser", "text": "Silithyst Geysers can be found throughout &lt;a href=\"Silithus\"&gt;Silithus&lt;/a&gt;. Picking one up will give you the &lt;a href=\"Silithyst\"&gt;Silithyst&lt;/a&gt; debuff, which will force one to travel at normal speeds no matter what. It will also flag the player for &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;.\nShould players drop the dust, a &lt;a href=\"Silithyst%20Mound\"&gt;Silithyst Mound&lt;/a&gt; will spawn at that location, which can then be picked up by any other player."}
{"id": "281145", "revid": "819614", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=281145", "title": "Silithyst Mound", "text": "When carrying &lt;a href=\"Silithyst\"&gt;Silithyst&lt;/a&gt; for the World PvP event &lt;a href=\"The%20Silithyst%20Must%20Flow\"&gt;The Silithyst Must Flow&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Silithyst%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Silithyst (quest)&lt;/a&gt; world quest during &lt;a href=\"Call%20of%20the%20Scarab\"&gt;Call of the Scarab&lt;/a&gt;, if a player mounts, dies, or cancels the buff, they will drop their silithyst on the ground, creating a small mound that anyone can pick up. Attacking an opposing faction player is a good way to save time when transporting silithyst, as they can carry it a great distance before they drop it."}
