{"id": "114011", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=114011", "title": "Silixiz's Tower Key", "text": "Silixiz's Tower Key can be &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pickpocket&lt;/a&gt;ed from &lt;a href=\"Foreman%20Silixiz\"&gt;Foreman Silixiz&lt;/a&gt; outside the tower north of &lt;a href=\"Sludge%20Fen\"&gt;Sludge Fen&lt;/a&gt; in the northeastern corner of the &lt;a href=\"Barrens\"&gt;Barrens&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen you defeat the boss of the quest, at the top of the tower, your player gets poisoned. The poison is special, last 7 days and prevents you from using stealth.\nThe poison is removed when you complete the next quest in the chain, or if you have a high(?) level player cast some form of remove poison spell.\nNotes.\nIf the foreman doesn't have the key on him, you'll probably need to kill him and wait for him to respawn.\nIf you don't pick pocket the key from the foreman (killing him doesn't give you the key, it must be pick pocketed) and kill the boss you will get a 7 day debuff, which prevents you from using stealth. This prevents you from using pick pocket on the foreman, making the quest impossible.\nThe solution to this is to have a high level healer cure you of the poison, then return and pick pocket the key.\nThe directions given to get to the next quest should be followed (southwest from the undead city, then east). If you take a shortcut and go straight south / southeast from the undead city to your destination you will pass through an area with much higher level enemies."}
{"id": "15395", "revid": "41171629", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15395", "title": "Silk", "text": "Silk is a type of fiber used in making textiles, and generally produced by &lt;a href=\"spider\"&gt;spider&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"moth\"&gt;moth&lt;/a&gt; larvae. The &lt;a href=\"Mok%27nathal\"&gt;Mok'nathal&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%27s%20Edge%20Mountains\"&gt;Blade's Edge Mountains&lt;/a&gt; harvest silk from the cocoons of wild moth larvae. The silk farms of &lt;a href=\"Pandaria\"&gt;Pandaria&lt;/a&gt;, such as the ancient and respected &lt;a href=\"Silken%20Fields\"&gt;Silken Fields&lt;/a&gt;, raise their own &lt;a href=\"silkworm\"&gt;silkworm&lt;/a&gt;s for silk production.\nHigh-ranking members of the &lt;a href=\"Defias%20Brotherhood\"&gt;Defias Brotherhood&lt;/a&gt; wear silk bandanas to signify their rank; other members' bandanas are made from materials like linen instead.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Shadowlands\"&gt;Shadowlands&lt;/a&gt;, the night fae of &lt;a href=\"Ardenweald\"&gt;Ardenweald&lt;/a&gt; gather silk from &lt;a href=\"silkstrider\"&gt;silkstrider&lt;/a&gt;s. Their main production hub is the &lt;a href=\"Gossamer%20Cliffs\"&gt;Gossamer Cliffs&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs a crafting reagent.\nThese reagents are primarily used by the &lt;a href=\"tailoring\"&gt;tailoring&lt;/a&gt; profession."}
