{"id": "744946", "revid": "27079649", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=744946", "title": "Silkstrider", "text": "Silkstriders (also written silk striders) are large, silk-producing &lt;a href=\"beast\"&gt;beast&lt;/a&gt;s native to &lt;a href=\"Ardenweald\"&gt;Ardenweald&lt;/a&gt;. They are domesticated by the &lt;a href=\"night%20fae\"&gt;night fae&lt;/a&gt;, who use their silk to craft music instruments, weapons, and tools. Despite its gossamer appearance, silkstrider thread possesses great tensile strength, allowing it to be used as a bowstring for war and merriment alike. For this reason, the animals are vital to Ardenweald; more important than almost anyone knows.\nSilkstriders are very delicate creatures and will not spin silk if they become stressed or frightened, so the night fae play music for them to keep them calm and happy. When content, they dance gracefully and make humming or chirping noises. The animals begin life as small larvae that hatch from cocoons. &lt;a href=\"Spriggan\"&gt;Spriggan&lt;/a&gt;s have been known to capture and eat silkstrider larvae.\nThe main silkstrider hub in Ardenweald is the &lt;a href=\"Gossamer%20Cliffs\"&gt;Gossamer Cliffs&lt;/a&gt;, which came under attack from &lt;a href=\"Blackthorn%20%28Ardenweald%29\"&gt;Blackthorn&lt;/a&gt; spriggans and &lt;a href=\"Mueh%27zala\"&gt;Mueh'zala&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"boggart\"&gt;boggart&lt;/a&gt; minions, putting a halt to production. The silkstriders' broodmother, &lt;a href=\"Ol%27%20Gertie\"&gt;Ol' Gertie&lt;/a&gt;, was killed by the boggart &lt;a href=\"Noisul%20of%20Many%20Faces\"&gt;Noisul of Many Faces&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;Adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s helped clear out the attackers and rescue the night fae caretakers to get the production up and running again. They also saved Gertie's larva, &lt;a href=\"Gertie%20Jr.\"&gt;Gertie Jr.&lt;/a&gt;, and brought her to the safety of the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Forest\"&gt;Heart of the Forest&lt;/a&gt; for the sake of Ardenweald's future."}
